  "source": "Lemma:\n. \"Lemma 4.5 (Pigeonhole Principle)\"\ngiven:\n. n is \\set.theoretic.natural.number\n. A is \\set\nwhere:\n. A \\:proper.subset:/ n\nthen:\n. not:\n  . n \\:equivalent:/ A\nDocumented:\n. description: \"If $n \\in \\omega$, then $n$ is not equivalent to any of its proper subsets. Equivalently, every injective function from $n$ to $n$ is surjective. This is proved by induction on $n$.\"\nId: \"a77ed390-76bd-4651-8b94-79dcf993f202\"",
